 World Briefs

 Pak slur irks Aziz 

 Washington, Jan. 24 (PTI): Dismissing former US diplomat Richard Holbrookes remarks that Pakistanis were weird people, Prime Minister Shaukat Aziz said his countrymen were promising and vibrant. 

He added that no society was immune from having different kinds of people. 

 Nepal clashes 

 Kathmandu (Reuters): Nepali riot police clashed with pro-democracy protesters in the capital for a fourth day on Tuesday, firing tear gas and using water cannons to beat back hundreds of demonstrators. 

 Lanka blasts 

 Colombo (Reuters): Five explosions rocked Sri Lankas capital on Tuesday, injuring no one but panicking the city as Norwegian peace broker Erik Solheim prepared to meet Tamil Tiger rebels in a last-ditch bid to salvage a 2002 truce. 




